.TH "pmcraid_check_ioctl_buffer" 9 "pmcraid_check_ioctl_buffer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pmcraid_check_ioctl_buffer \- check for proper access to user buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pmcraid_check_ioctl_buffer
.BI "(int cmd "  ","
.BI "void __user *arg "  ","
.BI "struct pmcraid_ioctl_header *hdr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cmd" 12
ioctl command
.IP "arg" 12
user buffer
.IP "hdr" 12
pointer to kernel memory for pmcraid_ioctl_header
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Return Value
negetive error code if there are access issues, otherwise zero.
Upon success, returns ioctl header copied out of user buffer.
